        "subject": "LU-874 obdfilter: reserve pages for each OSS thread.",
        "message": "LU-874 obdfilter: reserve pages for each OSS thread.\n\nReserve pages cache for each OSS threads during IO.\nNote: this patch will disable read-only cache for testing\npurpose. And also it is just a temporary patch, and not even\nclose for inspection, and I only made it pass sanity, which\nshould enough for this test. The purpose of it is to see whether\nit would help for fragmented IO and allievate the slow IO\nproblem, so we will have more information to know how to\ndeal with OSS memory.\n\nSigned-off-by: Wang Di <di.wang@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: Iebfa108a3f7006d08765967511b3bc90ebca3d30\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
